<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12071c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12071c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12071c"> 71(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ Depth of 1 man</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The angel, in order to avoid a contest between the people of different territories who would wish to become possessed of the Saint&apos;s relics, advised St. Patrick, first, that at his burial two young oxen were to be <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> permitted to stray about at will, but wherever they should finally halt should be selected as the place for his interment; secondly, he ordered that the Saint&apos;s body should be buried deep, to the height of a man in the earth, and that his remains should not be removed from this grave. <small> William Canon Fleming, <a name="WFSP" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WFSP"><cite title="source">The Life of St Patrick: Apostle of Ireland</cite></a> (1905) 159</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
